============================================================
PART 8: The key identity A^2 - A^{T2} = A^T - A
============================================================
  For regular tournaments:
  A^2 - (A^T)^2 = A^T - A = (J-I) - 2A
  Entry-wise for i!=j: (A^2)_{ij} - (A^2)_{ji} = A_{ji} - A_{ij}
  For edge i->j: lambda_{ij} = mu_{ij} + 1

